<subSubSection id="D594C9833BA63A886839D7C5FFB38F76" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5A876C2810179A60241E52D8BFF2189F" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B5832776378259018EFD213D1B01712" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
No genetic samples were available for 
<taxonomicName id="78D1833893F4A4C271C0163DDDE44FC3" genus="F." lsidName="F. granadensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis id="63EEA340A3E277D79E7C7130C01B179F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">F. granadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Warncke, 1987) or 
<taxonomicName id="79D15DA6C74A347A5AA13B8F53CA1D83" genus="F." lsidName="F. merceti" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="merceti">
<emphasis id="EE28986607C7225AF2AFC117EF48C9D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">F. merceti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Vachal, 1910). However, examination of males of these two species shows that they clearly belong in 
<taxonomicName id="2D607BA80B58451E6F3375EA217AE5BC" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavipanurgus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flavipanurgus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4531517A2020F1BA2894E6E1574E5BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Flavipanurgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: S7 is deeply excavated apicomedially, and the genital capsule has the gonocoxae lacking apical points along with flattened and apically spatulate gonostyli (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A514587DD315AD4F3065D97561E76E27" captionStart="Figures 31–32" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 31 - 32. Flavipanurgus male genitalia 31 Flavipanurgus granadensis 32 Flavipanurgus merceti." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.89.72083.figures31-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/650546" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">31-32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="931EA342916820A8AC47DBCA9E447404" doi="10.3897/jhr.89.72083.figures31-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/650546" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" start="Figures 31–32" startId="F8">
<paragraph id="8F095066645E23B3C6A5D1BCD8EBB6C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
